Sentencas: Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (SFM) is investigated as a novel electrode for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: CaxSr2-xFe1.5Mo0.5O6-delta (Ca-x-SFM) maintains the perovskite phase under both oxidizing and reducing atmospheres when the doping content x <= 0.50.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Ca doping significantly improves the conductivity, from 39.9 S cm(-1) for SFM to 55.7 S cm(-1) for Ca-0.25 -SFM, and 93.1 S cm(-1) for Ca-0.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: 5-SFM at 800 degrees C in hydrogen atmospheres.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Ca-0.(25)-SFM based symmetrical cell exhibits peak power densities of 709, 480, and 392 mW cm(-2) at 800 degrees C when hydrogen, the syngas, and carbon monoxide are tested as the fuel, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The interfacial polarization resistance for hydrogen oxidation reaction on Ca-0.25 -SFM anode is studied via a three-electrode system considering hydrogen concentration and temperature.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The impedance spectroscopy demonstrates a decreasing polarization resistance with increasing hydrogen content and temperature, as well as a nearly constant polarization resistance under variation of the water-vapor content.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The distribution of relaxation times analysis and reaction kinetics calculation confirms that the H-2 dissociated adsorption process is the rate-limiting step.
Titulo: Electrochemical performance and anode reaction process for Ca doped Sr2Fe1.5Mo0.5O6-δ as electrodes for symmetrical solid oxide fuel cells
